1 serving aging Vermonters in the program’s region. The Department shall
2 select one or more programs, as funding permits, to participate in the pilot
3 based on a program’s application materials. A successful application shall
4 include a plan to:
5 (1) create a community health worker position to serve program clients;
6 (2) expand the program’s nursing services to serve a greater percentage
7 of aging Vermonters in the program’s region, including ensuring that nurse
8 home visits are not limited in number or duration;
9 (3) identify and fill the program’s coverage gaps;
10 (4) integrate enhanced administrative support within the program; and
11 (5) develop a system to obtain relevant data and document program
12 needs, outcomes, and processes.
13 (c) On or before December 15, 2027, a program participating in the pilot
14 described in this section shall submit a report to the Department detailing the
15 number of aging Vermonters served, program gaps, recommended program
16 improvements, and any other data relevant to the pilot.
17 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
18 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
